<title class="- topic/title "><keyword class="- topic/keyword ">dita</keyword></title>
<shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">The &lt;<keyword class="- topic/keyword ">dita</keyword>&gt; element provides a top-level container
for multiple topics when you create documents using the ditabase document
type. The &lt;<keyword class="- topic/keyword ">dita</keyword>&gt; element lets you create any sequence
of concept, task, and reference topics, and the ditabase document type lets
you further nest these topic types inside each other. The &lt;<keyword class="- topic/keyword ">dita</keyword>&gt;
element has no particular output implications; it simply allows you to create
multiple topics of different types at the same level in a single document.</shortdesc>
<prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata ">
<keywords class="- topic/keywords "><indexterm class="- topic/indexterm ">dita</indexterm><indexterm class="- topic/indexterm ">Compound topics</indexterm>
</keywords>
</metadata></prolog>
<body class="- topic/body ">

<section class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Contained by</title>Not contained by any other element. The
root element for the compound DITA document type.</section>
<section class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Inheritance</title>Not a specializable DITA element.</section>

<example class="- topic/example ">     <title class="- topic/title ">Example</title>     <pre xml:space="preserve" class="- topic/pre ">&lt;dita&gt;
  &lt;concept id="batintro"&gt;...&lt;/concept&gt;
  &lt;reference id="batparts"&gt;...&lt;/reference&gt;
  &lt;task id="batfeeding"&gt;...&lt;/task&gt;
  &lt;task id="battraining"&gt;...&lt;/task&gt;
  &lt;task id="batcleanup"&gt;...&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;/dita&gt;</pre>       </example>
</body>
 
